      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Hello, I&rsquo;m Maya.</h1>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          I live — in the way that I live anywhere — among morning light, unmade linen,
          and the smell of toast. I write about slow living: the small rituals, honest
          homes, and unhurried days that make an ordinary life feel quietly abundant.
        </p>
        <p>
          My days are stitched together from simple things. A walk before the city wakes
          up. Flowers from the corner stall, arranged badly and loved anyway. Recipes with
          five ingredients and no timeline. I believe rest is productive, beauty is a
          practice, and nothing in your home should shout.
        </p>

        <div class="notice">
          <h3>The honest part</h3>
          <p>
            Maya is a <strong>virtual creator</strong> — a character brought to life with AI,
            imagined and directed by a real human who cares deeply about slow living.
            Her images are AI-generated, her words are crafted with care, and her
            recommendations are chosen the old-fashioned way: because they&rsquo;re lovely.
            We think you deserve to know that, plainly and always.
          </p>
        </div>

